1
00:00:00,500 --> 00:00:04,120
<i>In the name of God</i>

2
00:00:16,571 --> 00:00:21,506
Look at you!
What in the world are you looking at?

3
00:00:21,676 --> 00:00:24,025
Can't check out my own fiance?

4
00:00:24,190 --> 00:00:26,333
Put it away, it's embarrassing!

5
00:00:28,217 --> 00:00:32,993
- This one is nice. - Which one?
- The one we took on your roof.

6
00:00:34,079 --> 00:00:35,826
What class!

7
00:00:36,990 --> 00:00:38,545
What class!

8
00:00:44,488 --> 00:00:47,391
- Was that your foot?
- No, it was my chador.

9
00:00:50,708 --> 00:00:54,974
I've told you 100 times! Hold onto
your chador! Now what do do?

10
00:00:55,135 --> 00:00:56,008
Okay...

11
00:00:57,249 --> 00:00:58,916
Be careful, you'll rip it.

12
00:01:12,364 --> 00:01:14,507
There's nobody here at this hour.

13
00:01:14,677 --> 00:01:17,343
- Who are you hiding from?
- From you!

14
00:02:13,420 --> 00:02:16,051
- Don't go too fast!
- Alright. Go in already!

15
00:02:16,571 --> 00:02:18,793
- Hi!
- Hello, beautiful bride-to-be!

16
00:02:18,963 --> 00:02:20,711
- Are there many people?
- Lots.

17
00:02:24,346 --> 00:02:25,482
Hitchhiking on that
road is pretty shady.

18
00:02:25,483 --> 00:02:26,616
Especially for a girl.

19
00:02:26,778 --> 00:02:29,287
- They'll find her.
- Find her? Right, dream on.

20
00:02:29,650 --> 00:02:32,238
- Wasn't expecting you.
- There wasn't much snow.

21
00:02:32,402 --> 00:02:34,547
You need money to get married.

22
00:02:34,717 --> 00:02:37,165
If our pay was enough
to get married with,

23
00:02:37,166 --> 00:02:39,615
would've done it
100 times already!

24
00:02:40,259 --> 00:02:43,130
You've already buried
three husbands!

25
00:02:43,291 --> 00:02:46,319
- Didn't take any from you.
- Be my guest!

26
00:02:49,272 --> 00:02:50,463
Well, goodbye.

27
00:02:50,628 --> 00:02:53,577
Hurry up,
have to get back early.

28
00:02:53,818 --> 00:02:56,847
- Sit down, I'm going to try.
- Thank you.

29
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:03,384
I've brought it for you.
Do you want to try it on?

30
00:03:05,502 --> 00:03:10,359
- Is it our turn yet?
- So, which one of the two should go?

31
00:03:10,806 --> 00:03:13,711
Find a job for my wife and me.

32
00:03:15,113 --> 00:03:17,258
- Hi, granny.
- Hello.

33
00:03:49,410 --> 00:03:50,522
Wait!

34
00:03:51,564 --> 00:03:55,307
Where are you?
Congratulations.

35
00:03:55,752 --> 00:03:58,054
- When is it for?
- Next Friday.

36
00:03:58,224 --> 00:04:01,445
You'll have it by Thursday
and pay what you can.

37
00:04:01,614 --> 00:04:03,360
Thanks a lot.

38
00:04:06,678 --> 00:04:09,106
- Pick any one.
- Are you kidding me?

39
00:04:09,270 --> 00:04:11,018
I'm serious. Go on.

40
00:04:14,256 --> 00:04:17,601
- This one.
- Let me see. Heravi Square.

41
00:04:17,884 --> 00:04:20,595
- It's too far.
- The others are worse.

42
00:04:20,755 --> 00:04:22,866
- Show me.
- Go on.

43
00:04:24,225 --> 00:04:28,003
- Don't come back late.
- You got it. See you later.

44
00:07:01,233 --> 00:07:04,217
- Who is it?
- Excuse me, ma'am.

45
00:07:04,384 --> 00:07:08,046
Your neighbors aren't answering.
Do you know where they are?

46
00:07:08,331 --> 00:07:10,045
<i>Their buzzer's broken. You are...</i>

47
00:07:10,206 --> 00:07:12,872
I'm here to work for them.
Could you let me in?

48
00:07:13,037 --> 00:07:16,940
<i>I'll call them
and they'll let you in themselves.</i>

49
00:07:23,007 --> 00:07:24,719
- Give me the fish.
- Mom!

50
00:07:25,001 --> 00:07:26,907
Be good!
Hurry up!

51
00:07:29,507 --> 00:07:31,413
Be careful, you'll fall.

52
00:07:37,005 --> 00:07:38,514
Where are you going?

53
00:07:39,198 --> 00:07:41,864
- Are you looking for someone?
- Apartment 17.

54
00:07:42,029 --> 00:07:46,091
- Buzz and they'll let you in.
- It's already open.

55
00:07:46,257 --> 00:07:50,317
Don't know what you're doing here.
Go on. Step outside.

56
00:08:16,166 --> 00:08:17,392
Hold on.

57
00:08:20,594 --> 00:08:22,182
- Hello.
- Hello, come in.

58
00:08:22,348 --> 00:08:24,413
Swear, have the tickets already.

59
00:08:24,581 --> 00:08:28,087
You don't know how long I've
wanted to go away with my family.

60
00:08:28,649 --> 00:08:30,873
Yeah, right...
Leave me alone!

61
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:34,374
Fine, okay. Five minutes?

62
00:08:34,870 --> 00:08:38,172
Know it'll last until midnight!

63
00:08:42,727 --> 00:08:44,394
Okay. Bye.

64
00:08:47,991 --> 00:08:49,738
Miss?

65
00:08:52,100 --> 00:08:56,204
- Yes.
- Stan with this room.

66
00:08:56,645 --> 00:08:59,628
My wife will tell you
what to do afterward

67
00:08:59,795 --> 00:09:01,428
What a mess!

68
00:09:03,346 --> 00:09:05,296
Wait a minute.

69
00:09:07,731 --> 00:09:12,077
Put on these slippers.
There's glass, you might get hurt.

70
00:09:26,476 --> 00:09:31,059
Why do you have my cell?
Why'd you take it?

71
00:09:31,780 --> 00:09:34,922
Have things to do.
have to go.

72
00:09:35,090 --> 00:09:38,310
I've been looking for you
for an hour.

73
00:09:38,518 --> 00:09:39,789
When are you coming back?

74
00:09:39,955 --> 00:09:44,776
- Sir? - Hello, yes?
- The broom and dustpan?

75
00:09:44,940 --> 00:09:46,573
Just a second.

76
00:09:48,090 --> 00:09:49,723
Over there.

77
00:09:52,715 --> 00:09:57,140
It's the cleaning lady called.
Specialized agencies send them over.

78
00:09:58,698 --> 00:10:01,409
So, they'll work together!

79
00:10:36,305 --> 00:10:38,415
She parked in front of the gate again!

80
00:10:41,010 --> 00:10:43,381
- You shouldn't have called her.
- My cell?

81
00:10:43,382 --> 00:10:45,753
- The concierge was
going to help me.

82
00:10:45,916 --> 00:10:48,287
It's been a damn mess
for three days now.

83
00:10:48,288 --> 00:10:50,657
The concierge, the concierge...

84
00:10:51,739 --> 00:10:54,087
- My phone?
- Where are you going?

85
00:10:54,252 --> 00:10:57,121
- Give it to me, have to run.
- Run where?

86
00:10:57,720 --> 00:11:00,669
- To work. What do you think?
- Today?

87
00:11:01,350 --> 00:11:03,810
Mahmud called.
They have some problems.

88
00:11:04,380 --> 00:11:08,124
- We were supposed to talk.
- I'll be back. I'm not running away.

89
00:11:10,163 --> 00:11:12,227
You said we'd talk it over today.

90
00:11:13,472 --> 00:11:17,454
Know did,
but that damn Mahmud needs me.

91
00:11:17,859 --> 00:11:21,557
Don't worry, I'll be back by 5
and we'll take care of everything.

92
00:11:21,728 --> 00:11:25,631
- You said that this morning!
- Yes, did say that. You're right!

93
00:11:25,796 --> 00:11:27,622
But they need me.

94
00:11:27,789 --> 00:11:30,694
That's just great!
You always have time for Mahmud!

95
00:11:31,499 --> 00:11:35,163
- Amir-Ali's not home. - And, so?
- don't want to talk in front of him.

96
00:11:35,327 --> 00:11:38,787
What's the problem of talking
in front of him?

97
00:11:39,195 --> 00:11:41,465
We have to make a decision.

98
00:11:41,628 --> 00:11:43,738
Decide for yourself.
I've already decided.

99
00:11:44,459 --> 00:11:46,251
Then I'm not going tomorrow.

100
00:11:48,568 --> 00:11:51,154
What are you saying?
Mojdeh?

101
00:11:52,316 --> 00:11:55,980
Listen. have the tickets.
I'm not your puppet.

102
00:11:56,144 --> 00:11:58,969
You promised.
Don't go back on your word.

103
00:11:59,135 --> 00:12:01,687
All promised you
was a trip to Dubai.

104
00:12:01,846 --> 00:12:04,116
Kept my promise,
you're full of shit!

105
00:12:04,280 --> 00:12:06,991
- Watch your language.
- Look who's talking.

106
00:12:07,151 --> 00:12:10,418
The guy begged me
to come and help him.

107
00:12:10,580 --> 00:12:13,087
It's urgent and you want me to stay.

108
00:12:13,253 --> 00:12:15,634
- Didn't say anything.
- Yesterday, you said enough.

109
00:12:15,805 --> 00:12:17,472
You're the one who said too much.

110
00:12:19,474 --> 00:12:21,346
You so damn neurotic!

111
00:12:23,542 --> 00:12:24,653
Idiot.

112
00:12:26,653 --> 00:12:28,241
Wait.

113
00:12:29,484 --> 00:12:34,746
I'm speaking to you. If you leave,
I'll take Amir-Ali and go.

114
00:12:34,908 --> 00:12:37,130
- You're a disgrace!
- Disgrace! I'm not moving

115
00:12:37,299 --> 00:12:42,315
Wait! swear I'll take him away.
Why won't you understand?

116
00:12:59,274 --> 00:13:00,987
Mrs. Sabri?

117
00:13:12,514 --> 00:13:15,180
- Hello, ma'am.
- Hello. Call your wife.

118
00:13:15,346 --> 00:13:18,613
- She won't be long.
- She was supposed to help me.

119
00:13:18,776 --> 00:13:21,027
- She's out shopping
for the Razavi family.

120
00:13:21,028 --> 00:13:23,279
- Tell her to come see me.

121
00:13:23,441 --> 00:13:26,232
The management won't allow
my wife to work.

122
00:13:26,393 --> 00:13:28,422
It's none of their business.

123
00:13:28,945 --> 00:13:34,129
When she works, take care of the kids.
They say it keeps me from my work.

124
00:13:34,288 --> 00:13:37,669
Tell her to come up.
I'll take care of it.

125
00:13:50,878 --> 00:13:53,465
- Is your mother home?
- Yes, come in.

126
00:13:54,787 --> 00:13:56,613
Mom, it's Mrs. Samii.

127
00:14:03,999 --> 00:14:06,143
Mojdeh, dear, come in!

128
00:14:06,950 --> 00:14:10,648
- Thanks. ls Sabri here?
- No, why?

129
00:14:10,818 --> 00:14:13,167
- She was supposed to help me.

130
00:14:13,168 --> 00:14:15,514
- The management doesn't
want her to work.

131
00:14:16,083 --> 00:14:18,635
Tell her to see me
when she finishes your shopping.

132
00:14:18,795 --> 00:14:21,936
- Let's keep this between us.
- Okay.

133
00:14:22,104 --> 00:14:24,929
They talked about her
in the meeting.

134
00:14:26,651 --> 00:14:28,239
Well? What happened?

135
00:14:28,406 --> 00:14:32,025
They're going to tell the landlord
to take care of it.

136
00:14:34,148 --> 00:14:37,336
Don't worry about it.
We know nothing. Come in.

137
00:14:37,498 --> 00:14:40,958
- Have to run. Tell her to come up.
- Bye.

138
00:14:59,910 --> 00:15:01,657
Hello, ma'am.

139
00:15:03,340 --> 00:15:05,212
I'm looking for bleach.

140
00:15:05,853 --> 00:15:07,123
Come here.

141
00:15:08,963 --> 00:15:11,028
Didn't see any in the kitchen.

142
00:15:11,755 --> 00:15:15,101
I'm going to do the dishes
in the bathtub.

143
00:15:15,266 --> 00:15:18,486
That way, I'll make some room here.

144
00:15:18,655 --> 00:15:21,558
It's okay. Thanks a lot.

145
00:15:22,283 --> 00:15:25,902
- How much do owe you?
- What? haven't even started yet!

146
00:15:26,351 --> 00:15:28,620
Know. Someone's
coming by to help.

147
00:15:28,783 --> 00:15:33,162
- Then why did you call the agency?
- My husband did.

148
00:15:33,329 --> 00:15:38,185
- What difference does that make?
- don't owe you an explanation.

149
00:15:38,396 --> 00:15:40,346
- I'm sorry.
- I've changed my mind.

150
00:15:40,509 --> 00:15:43,083
Didn't go through your drawer.

151
00:15:43,180 --> 00:15:46,253
Was cleaning in the
room and it just fell out.

152
00:15:46,690 --> 00:15:48,358
Will five thousand Tomans do?

153
00:15:49,602 --> 00:15:53,469
Five thousand? But why?
came all this way!

154
00:15:53,868 --> 00:15:55,739
It's not enough? How much then?

155
00:15:55,902 --> 00:16:00,326
Can't accept this money
when didn't do anything.

156
00:16:01,325 --> 00:16:05,625
Take it. Someone else
is coming to do it.

157
00:16:06,550 --> 00:16:09,816
Did do something wrong?
What happened?

158
00:16:10,099 --> 00:16:12,131
No. Are you going
to take it or what?

159
00:16:12,611 --> 00:16:14,836
She has three days of work here.

160
00:16:15,005 --> 00:16:17,465
- Don't care.
- I'll help you.

161
00:16:19,471 --> 00:16:21,774
You don't want it?
It's up to you.

162
00:16:33,868 --> 00:16:35,818
Close the door behind you.

163
00:16:48,025 --> 00:16:51,530
- Yes?
- Why isn't anyone answering?

164
00:16:51,695 --> 00:16:56,991
- Their buzzer doesn't work.
- Fix it. You're wasting people's time!

165
00:17:02,701 --> 00:17:04,890
- Yes?
- There's a gentleman here for you.

166
00:17:05,333 --> 00:17:07,885
- Who is it?
- The glass cutter.

167
00:17:09,559 --> 00:17:11,546
Tell him I'm coming.

168
00:17:14,466 --> 00:17:16,893
You parked in front of the gate again!

169
00:17:17,058 --> 00:17:20,121
What do you mean?
They want to park a truck?

170
00:17:22,163 --> 00:17:25,383
- Who gave me a flat?
- don't know.

171
00:17:25,552 --> 00:17:28,581
How should know?
Give me the keys.

172
00:17:28,743 --> 00:17:32,201
I'll do it. just want
to see if it's the psycho!

173
00:17:32,451 --> 00:17:36,478
- Saw her come in.
- Their buzzer doesn't work.

174
00:17:36,638 --> 00:17:38,908
- Forget it.
Are you looking for trouble?

175
00:17:38,909 --> 00:17:41,175
- She doesn't scare me.

176
00:18:00,248 --> 00:18:02,471
Don't forget our New Year's gifts.

177
00:19:09,119 --> 00:19:10,789
Mrs. Sami!

178
00:19:14,066 --> 00:19:15,574
Miss?

179
00:19:17,613 --> 00:19:19,328
Someone's calling you.

180
00:19:22,560 --> 00:19:24,148
What's wrong?

181
00:19:29,139 --> 00:19:32,759
- Did anybody call this morning?
- No. Nobody.

182
00:19:33,487 --> 00:19:35,075
When my husband was there?

183
00:19:35,241 --> 00:19:37,952
When got there,
he was on the phone.

184
00:19:38,272 --> 00:19:40,303
- Who was it?
- What do you mean?

185
00:19:41,303 --> 00:19:44,446
- What was he saying?
- don't know, ma'am.

186
00:19:50,596 --> 00:19:51,662
Sorry...

187
00:19:56,975 --> 00:19:58,245
Listen!

188
00:19:59,687 --> 00:20:01,320
Come here!

189
00:20:02,320 --> 00:20:03,953
Said come here.

190
00:20:05,509 --> 00:20:07,859
- Who is it?
- Hello, ma'am.

191
00:20:08,023 --> 00:20:09,735
<i>Hello. May he-[0 you?</i>

192
00:20:09,897 --> 00:20:12,687
wanted to make an appointment
at the salon.

193
00:20:13,087 --> 00:20:16,276
<i>- Your name?
- Ruhangiz Barati</i>

194
00:20:16,438 --> 00:20:19,421
<i>- Is this your first time?
- Yes.</i>

195
00:20:19,627 --> 00:20:21,374
<i>Who referred you?</i>

196
00:20:24,334 --> 00:20:26,126
Madame Rahimi.

197
00:20:26,287 --> 00:20:29,192
<i>I'm busy now.
Can you this afternoon?</i>

198
00:20:29,677 --> 00:20:33,058
- Around what time?
- 5 p. m.

199
00:20:33,227 --> 00:20:38,127
<i>Otherwise, go for a walk
and come back in 30 minutes.</i>

200
00:20:42,080 --> 00:20:46,537
<i>- What about between 2 and 5?
-  can't; I'll be out.</i>

201
00:20:46,706 --> 00:20:49,259
Okay, well then perhaps
in 30 minutes.

202
00:20:49,816 --> 00:20:52,881
<i>- Thanks, it's very nice.
- You're welcome.</i>

203
00:20:56,795 --> 00:21:00,573
- Was good?
- Yes, thank you.

204
00:21:00,943 --> 00:21:02,768
Thank you, God.

205
00:21:12,149 --> 00:21:14,020
The other one is also ?at.

206
00:21:14,941 --> 00:21:16,812
Why is it so expensive?

207
00:21:17,134 --> 00:21:20,560
If you only knew how far
I've come in this cold.

208
00:21:20,723 --> 00:21:23,151
You still haven't taken
the trash down?

209
00:21:23,316 --> 00:21:24,791
You live far from here.

210
00:21:24,950 --> 00:21:26,425
Was busy, I'll do it.

211
00:21:26,586 --> 00:21:29,218
Don't forget our New Year's gifts.

212
00:21:34,721 --> 00:21:38,022
- Should we hang the curtains?
- We can't do it alone.

213
00:21:40,265 --> 00:21:44,292
- Why don't you call your husband?
- He doesn't even reach my waist!

214
00:21:46,166 --> 00:21:48,674
- What is it?
- New Year's gifts for the kids?

215
00:21:48,839 --> 00:21:52,026
Paid twice as much
and you want presents as well?

216
00:21:56,056 --> 00:21:57,883
Why is the water running?

217
00:21:59,366 --> 00:22:02,748
- This bucket is still dirty.
- I'll wash it.

218
00:22:03,036 --> 00:22:05,498
Want the girl to come and help?

219
00:22:06,785 --> 00:22:08,611
Which girl?

220
00:22:09,177 --> 00:22:12,160
- The one that was here.
- The cleaning lady?

221
00:22:15,758 --> 00:22:19,262
- Why is she still here?
- She has an appointment at the salon.

222
00:22:19,866 --> 00:22:23,008
- The salon?
- She's getting married soon.

223
00:22:23,933 --> 00:22:26,315
She's going to have
her eyebrows done.

224
00:22:28,918 --> 00:22:32,378
It's cold outside,
tell her to come up.

225
00:22:33,983 --> 00:22:36,773
Do you know how much
she's going to pay you?

226
00:22:37,532 --> 00:22:39,484
I'm totally lost.

227
00:22:39,646 --> 00:22:43,787
This morning, she gave me five
thousand Tomans and asked me to leave.

228
00:22:44,391 --> 00:22:48,010
- They're strange. Are they fighting?
- We can't take it any more.

229
00:22:48,180 --> 00:22:52,082
Last night, her husband went mad
and broke the window.

230
00:22:52,249 --> 00:22:54,199
Saw the broken glass.

231
00:22:55,040 --> 00:22:58,782
It's always the same thing.
Are you afraid with your husband?

232
00:22:58,946 --> 00:23:04,686
- No, he's not at all like that.
- No offense.

233
00:23:05,129 --> 00:23:09,395
- Is your husband like that?
- God forbid! wouldn't say that.

234
00:23:12,189 --> 00:23:15,647
My husband is madly
in love with me!

235
00:23:15,816 --> 00:23:20,116
Nasser, my cousin,
was also in love with me.

236
00:23:22,437 --> 00:23:25,738
- When's it for?
- One more month.

237
00:23:29,814 --> 00:23:31,165
Is it expensive?

238
00:23:32,168 --> 00:23:34,437
- What?
- The hairdresser.

239
00:23:34,800 --> 00:23:36,512
Simine is very fair.

240
00:23:36,674 --> 00:23:39,702
Explain your situation
and she'll charge less.

241
00:23:39,864 --> 00:23:41,770
Why don't you call Mom...

242
00:23:43,334 --> 00:23:46,917
It's ringing.
Hello? Hi Mom. How are you?

243
00:23:47,241 --> 00:23:49,035
- It's Mahdi.
- Is it for me?

244
00:23:55,896 --> 00:24:00,081
- What are you waiting for?
- You knew wouldn't come up

245
00:24:00,244 --> 00:24:04,464
- Hurry, we have lots to do.
- You have to make up with her today.

246
00:24:05,387 --> 00:24:07,497
Okay. Be careful going down.

247
00:24:12,365 --> 00:24:17,347
- Still not finished.
- No need to take off your shoes.

248
00:24:17,910 --> 00:24:21,176
- Could've picked you up.
- Ahmad is downstairs.

249
00:24:23,533 --> 00:24:25,961
- Who is that?
- She's helping me.

250
00:24:27,041 --> 00:24:30,468
Ahmad is staying downstairs
like always.

251
00:24:30,631 --> 00:24:33,218
- If it bothers you, get him.
- Me?

252
00:24:33,383 --> 00:24:35,287
It's about time! It's been a year!

253
00:24:36,613 --> 00:24:38,757
He got worked up by himself.
He'll come back when he's ready.

254
00:24:39,245 --> 00:24:40,878
Just like kids!

255
00:24:41,039 --> 00:24:42,913
What's this mess?

256
00:24:43,075 --> 00:24:44,628
Still haven't finished?

257
00:24:44,789 --> 00:24:46,932
Heat it up, we'll eat it.

258
00:24:47,819 --> 00:24:51,200
You're the kid.
You never take things seriously.

259
00:24:51,370 --> 00:24:53,274
And what about you, Mrs. Serious?

260
00:24:53,642 --> 00:24:57,511
Have you looked in the mirror?
There's a salon next door!

261
00:24:59,265 --> 00:25:03,088
Excuse me. I'd like to get
my husband's permission.

262
00:25:05,127 --> 00:25:07,680
- His permission? - For the salon.
- No need.

263
00:25:07,840 --> 00:25:10,822
She's getting married.
She wants to get her eyebrows done.

264
00:25:11,269 --> 00:25:13,061
Don't tell him everything...
No tea for me.

265
00:25:14,021 --> 00:25:15,813
Surprise him.

266
00:25:16,613 --> 00:25:18,916
Do as you please.

267
00:25:22,276 --> 00:25:23,988
Didn't get any fruit.

268
00:25:24,469 --> 00:25:26,500
<i>You're so busy!</i>

269
00:25:27,022 --> 00:25:30,367
Will you be ready for Dubai,
with this mess?

270
00:25:30,810 --> 00:25:33,839
- Ma'am, shouldn't call him?
- It's up to you, he's your husband.

271
00:25:34,001 --> 00:25:36,950
You should've picked
a better country.

272
00:25:37,112 --> 00:25:39,778
- He didn't even want Dubai.
- Why Dubai?

273
00:25:40,023 --> 00:25:42,672
- Think about Amir-Ali.

274
00:25:42,673 --> 00:25:45,320
- Amir-Ali will grow up
like other children.

275
00:25:45,487 --> 00:25:47,391
Anyway, I'm not sure we're leaving.

276
00:25:47,839 --> 00:25:49,824
What do you mean, not leaving?

277
00:25:50,032 --> 00:25:54,253
Don't know. We'll see.
Take this when you leave.

278
00:25:54,578 --> 00:25:58,038
- Know how stubborn you can be.
- What do you mean?

279
00:25:58,208 --> 00:26:01,236
You didn't see Amir-Ali sleeping.

280
00:26:02,795 --> 00:26:04,540
You're going to be late.

281
00:26:04,708 --> 00:26:09,767
<i>He was so frightened.
He said he was dreaming about hell.</i>

282
00:26:10,450 --> 00:26:14,229
They lectured the kids on hell
at school for an hour.

283
00:26:15,157 --> 00:26:18,300
He can't even play
without me keeping an eye on him.

284
00:26:18,467 --> 00:26:20,575
Have to take him to school.

285
00:26:20,740 --> 00:26:22,771
I'm turning it off,
the handles are burning.

286
00:26:22,933 --> 00:26:26,553
- One more window and I'll go.
- You'll miss your appointment.

287
00:26:26,722 --> 00:26:28,911
There's danger everywhere.

288
00:26:29,074 --> 00:26:32,738
I'm always worried
when leave the house.

289
00:26:33,421 --> 00:26:37,368
In fact, one of my co-workers
disappeared the other night.

290
00:26:37,528 --> 00:26:40,796
- Don't tell her where you were.
- Why not?

291
00:26:41,477 --> 00:26:45,538
- Mrs. Rahimi referred you.
- Ah, forgot.

292
00:26:45,704 --> 00:26:48,212
You don't need that.
It's right over there.

293
00:26:48,376 --> 00:26:50,883
- Goodbye, ma'am.
- Goodbye.

294
00:26:55,834 --> 00:26:57,580
Why don't you answer?

295
00:26:59,065 --> 00:27:01,368
Don't lie.
What are you doing?

296
00:27:03,331 --> 00:27:07,075
Oh yeah? can see from here.

297
00:27:08,834 --> 00:27:10,390
Listen.

298
00:27:12,424 --> 00:27:14,011
Hello, ma'am.

299
00:27:14,418 --> 00:27:16,245
Come up for a minute.

300
00:27:16,612 --> 00:27:20,479
When do you count on making peace?
They're leaving tomorrow.

301
00:27:31,167 --> 00:27:32,279
What are you doing?

302
00:27:33,680 --> 00:27:35,711
I'm coming.

303
00:27:40,978 --> 00:27:44,040
What's all this about?
What happened this time?

304
00:27:45,723 --> 00:27:49,592
Are you hiding something from me?
Look at me.

305
00:27:54,178 --> 00:27:56,526
- Did Morteza call?

306
00:27:56,527 --> 00:27:58,875
- Poor guy, he was on
the verge of tears.

307
00:27:59,522 --> 00:28:04,741
Why are acting like this?
You're ruining you life!

308
00:28:06,660 --> 00:28:08,373
Mrs. Sabri?

309
00:28:10,091 --> 00:28:12,314
Clean the living room windows first.

310
00:28:12,483 --> 00:28:14,070
Come see.

311
00:28:20,778 --> 00:28:24,761
Mojdeh, you were doing so well
over these past months.

312
00:28:26,002 --> 00:28:27,715
Did something happen?

313
00:28:31,985 --> 00:28:34,095
Didn't know what he was up to!

314
00:28:37,608 --> 00:28:39,750
What are you talking about?
Poor guy!

315
00:28:40,160 --> 00:28:43,381
He works hard day and night
for you and Amir-Ali.

316
00:28:44,029 --> 00:28:45,980
He thinks I'm an idiot.

317
00:28:46,142 --> 00:28:49,204
He's not a fool.
Why would he leave you?

318
00:28:49,372 --> 00:28:51,039
And for whom?

319
00:28:52,763 --> 00:28:56,381
Mojdeh, patience has limits.

320
00:28:56,710 --> 00:28:59,853
One day, he'll leave you alone
with your kid.

321
00:29:00,379 --> 00:29:02,046
To hell with him!

322
00:29:04,725 --> 00:29:06,734
Come on. Go make up with Ahmad.

323
00:29:06,840 --> 00:29:09,550
You'll need a place to
stay if you fight with him.

324
00:29:10,507 --> 00:29:12,494
You don't have anyone besides us.

325
00:29:16,449 --> 00:29:20,397
You're the fool!
Such a sweet and kind husband!

326
00:29:20,798 --> 00:29:25,221
Don't defend him without
knowing him! know my husband!

327
00:29:31,804 --> 00:29:33,789
Wish Dad was here.

328
00:29:40,818 --> 00:29:42,927
Have you noticed anything recently?

329
00:29:46,520 --> 00:29:49,072
- I've heard things.
- From whom?

330
00:29:49,471 --> 00:29:51,026
What difference does it make?

331
00:29:51,186 --> 00:29:55,169
You want to ruin you life
because of gossip?

332
00:29:55,334 --> 00:29:59,234
It's one of our neighbors.
She heard Morteza's voice

333
00:29:59,401 --> 00:30:02,191
on that bitch's answering machine.

334
00:30:04,744 --> 00:30:06,650
Maybe she made a mistake.

335
00:30:10,487 --> 00:30:14,071
- I'm sure of it.
- How can you be sure?

336
00:30:17,747 --> 00:30:20,331
He smells like her perfume.

337
00:30:26,160 --> 00:30:28,429
That's all you needed.

338
00:30:29,072 --> 00:30:33,371
And with someone here!
Behind these walls, under my nose.

339
00:30:36,808 --> 00:30:39,553
Try to think
about your trip tomorrow.

340
00:30:39,919 --> 00:30:43,300
Leave all this till
after the holidays.

341
00:30:45,303 --> 00:30:48,047
Darling, don't get all worked up.

342
00:30:48,214 --> 00:30:52,955
- Have to settle this tonight.
- What are you going to do tonight?

343
00:30:55,471 --> 00:30:58,059
Your brother-in-law keeps honking.

344
00:30:58,223 --> 00:31:01,603
- Go, he's waiting for you.
- can't leave you like this.

345
00:31:02,251 --> 00:31:04,804
Go on.

346
00:31:04,964 --> 00:31:07,516
Don't get yourself all worked up.

347
00:31:07,675 --> 00:31:09,389
It'll be fine.

348
00:31:11,384 --> 00:31:13,131
Give me a kiss.

349
00:31:14,814 --> 00:31:18,002
- Happy New Year, anyway.
- Thanks.

350
00:31:29,012 --> 00:31:33,117
- What's wrong with you?
- I've been waiting an hour for you!

351
00:31:43,926 --> 00:31:48,782
You have good taste. can see
he's mischievous. Isn't he?

352
00:31:49,071 --> 00:31:52,496
It took my father two years
to accept this marriage.

353
00:31:55,052 --> 00:31:58,353
He was so persistent,
my dad finally accepted.

354
00:31:58,522 --> 00:32:02,549
- Hair colon'?
- No. That would be too much for him!

355
00:32:04,025 --> 00:32:05,773
Does he love you?

356
00:32:07,137 --> 00:32:08,691
Let me see.

357
00:32:11,604 --> 00:32:13,191
Do you like it?

358
00:32:13,916 --> 00:32:15,424
Thank you so much.

359
00:32:15,591 --> 00:32:17,893
- Tea?
- I'll make it.

360
00:32:18,063 --> 00:32:20,854
Since when do customers make tea?

361
00:32:36,768 --> 00:32:41,305
- Ma'am'? - Yes.
- What's your perfume?

362
00:32:42,111 --> 00:32:44,981
I'd like to find the same but for men.

363
00:32:45,462 --> 00:32:49,520
It was a gift.
It's the blue bottle in front of you.

364
00:33:02,888 --> 00:33:05,031
Don't get pregnant too soon now!

365
00:33:05,242 --> 00:33:09,541
He's in such a rush, I'm sure
I'll have twins on our wedding day!

366
00:33:10,784 --> 00:33:12,769
Do you have children?

367
00:33:21,831 --> 00:33:24,497
- Hello.
- Hello, come in.

368
00:33:24,662 --> 00:33:27,793
Just wanted to quickly
visit the apartment.

369
00:33:27,894 --> 00:33:29,128
Now?

370
00:33:29,289 --> 00:33:32,397
- I'll explain... Please come in.
- Sorry to bother you.

371
00:33:36,188 --> 00:33:38,955
Here's the kitchen.

372
00:33:39,260 --> 00:33:42,527
There's a terrace in the back.

373
00:33:52,698 --> 00:33:56,283
- Have you already found something?
- Found what?

374
00:33:56,448 --> 00:33:59,476
Can you move out now
or are you still looking?

375
00:33:59,916 --> 00:34:02,140
Don't live here.

376
00:34:05,142 --> 00:34:07,330
It's full of light, Mom.

377
00:34:12,797 --> 00:34:16,303
- Do you want to raise the rent?
- It has nothing to do about that.

378
00:34:17,184 --> 00:34:20,088
- So then?
- have some problems. need the money.

379
00:34:20,254 --> 00:34:23,204
Thank you, Mr. Razaghi.
We'll be in touch.

380
00:34:23,366 --> 00:34:25,554
Just the garage and I'll be right back.

381
00:34:28,231 --> 00:34:30,535
- Thank you, ma'am.
- Goodbye.

382
00:34:30,943 --> 00:34:34,210
- You didn't want to sell it!
- Now do.

383
00:34:34,372 --> 00:34:37,594
Already told you. have worries.
need money.

384
00:34:38,042 --> 00:34:42,737
I'm sick and tired
of all the complaints about you.

385
00:34:43,226 --> 00:34:46,527
- Who has complained?
- The neighbors.

386
00:34:46,695 --> 00:34:49,644
Why don't they tell me?

387
00:34:50,525 --> 00:34:53,587
- This is an apartment. - Yeah, and?
- You've opened a hair salon!

388
00:34:56,665 --> 00:34:58,254
I'll be right there!

389
00:34:58,420 --> 00:35:00,133
Sorry for having bothered you.

390
00:35:01,132 --> 00:35:06,146
Is there a problem with my salon?
don't bother anyone!

391
00:35:06,316 --> 00:35:10,219
- What's the problem?
- The neighbors are complaining.

392
00:35:10,385 --> 00:35:12,938
Too many strangers. Brides...

393
00:35:13,096 --> 00:35:15,887
They don't dare tell you themselves.
They tell me.

394
00:35:16,047 --> 00:35:18,838
Some car stereos
were stolen last week.

395
00:35:18,999 --> 00:35:23,297
- By my customers?
- You don't know all of them.

396
00:35:23,464 --> 00:35:25,655
- For example, do you
know this young lady?

397
00:35:25,656 --> 00:35:27,843
- She's my niece.

398
00:35:28,249 --> 00:35:31,790
Sorry. didn't mean any harm.
Usually speaking...

399
00:35:32,278 --> 00:35:34,468
- Some tea, Auntie?
- Yes, darling.

400
00:35:34,631 --> 00:35:38,500
- Didn't even offer you any teal
- Thanks, but they're waiting for me.

401
00:35:38,659 --> 00:35:43,514
Just a sec.
Tell me who complained.

402
00:35:43,883 --> 00:35:47,785
As soon as a woman lives alone,
people say slanderous things.

403
00:35:48,110 --> 00:35:52,887
Want this to be clear.
don't make any noise in this building.

404
00:35:53,334 --> 00:35:56,999
Okay, won't lie,
last wee had a bride...

405
00:35:57,283 --> 00:36:00,946
and there was a little music.
Not even 10 minutes.

406
00:36:01,111 --> 00:36:04,730
When my neighbors have parties,
never complain.

407
00:36:04,899 --> 00:36:08,200
- We'll talk tomorrow.
- Everyone leaves on vacation tomorrow.

408
00:36:08,369 --> 00:36:13,224
Upstairs they're going to Yazd.
Just across they're leaving at 4.

409
00:36:13,394 --> 00:36:17,172
Everyone will be gone.
Let's settle this now.

410
00:36:18,579 --> 00:36:20,167
This lighter doesn't work.

411
00:36:22,088 --> 00:36:23,916
I'll get in touch with you later.

412
00:36:24,402 --> 00:36:26,590
As if didn't have enough problems.

413
00:36:26,755 --> 00:36:29,386
Ma'am, the lighter doesn't work.

414
00:36:29,985 --> 00:36:32,446
If you don't mind, must go.

415
00:36:32,617 --> 00:36:35,566
- First have some tea.
- No, thanks.

416
00:36:36,844 --> 00:36:40,906
- Don't forget your photos!
- won't. But tell me...

417
00:36:41,589 --> 00:36:45,173
- How much do owe you?
- Keep your money.

418
00:36:46,575 --> 00:36:50,635
We'll worry about that when
you come on your wedding day.

419
00:36:50,802 --> 00:36:52,833
Wouldn't dare come back.

420
00:36:52,995 --> 00:36:55,548
Have you ever seen
a niece pay her aunt?

421
00:36:57,143 --> 00:36:59,808
- It's not done.
- So, it's my New Year's gift.

422
00:36:59,974 --> 00:37:01,958
I'm not really comfortable with this.

423
00:37:03,404 --> 00:37:05,275
But, thanks a lot.

424
00:37:20,992 --> 00:37:22,420
Ma.
am!

425
00:37:29,924 --> 00:37:32,193
- Have you forgotten something?
- No.

426
00:37:32,715 --> 00:37:37,094
That gentleman who was here earlier
asking you to leave...

427
00:37:37,580 --> 00:37:40,167
I'm sorry, but overheard you.

428
00:37:40,533 --> 00:37:43,323
Think your next door neighbor
was involved.

429
00:37:43,484 --> 00:37:46,194
- Which one?
- The one across from you.

430
00:37:46,554 --> 00:37:49,458
- You know them?
- This morning, came to work for them.

431
00:37:51,778 --> 00:37:54,683
- You're the one who buzzed?
- Yes.

432
00:37:55,128 --> 00:37:58,157
- She asked you to come here?
- No, came on my own.

433
00:37:58,397 --> 00:38:03,821
- Didn't Mrs. Rahimi refer you?
- Yes, it was her.

434
00:38:05,058 --> 00:38:09,199
Saw her this morning
having her tires changed.

435
00:38:09,366 --> 00:38:13,631
She was furious.
I'm sure it was her.

436
00:38:15,466 --> 00:38:19,164
Don't know them. They don't
seem to be that kind of people.

437
00:38:19,654 --> 00:38:24,555
Hardly see her. bumped into
her husband. He seems serious.

438
00:38:24,719 --> 00:38:26,512
The lady is kind of strange.

439
00:38:26,673 --> 00:38:31,018
Barely arrived when suddenly
she fired me and paid me.

440
00:38:31,179 --> 00:38:32,324
Why?

441
00:38:32,495 --> 00:38:36,193
She didn't trust me.
She was afraid might steal from her.

442
00:38:36,962 --> 00:38:42,497
Don't know anyone here.
They're all just acquaintances.

443
00:38:42,905 --> 00:38:46,206
But this lady doesn't trust anybody.

444
00:38:47,211 --> 00:38:50,478
When you go home,
try not to upset her.

445
00:38:50,641 --> 00:38:54,702
Don't want to cause any trouble.
Don't worry.

446
00:39:04,000 --> 00:39:07,188
Sabri, come get your child,
he keeps crying.

447
00:39:07,669 --> 00:39:08,986
Take him down.

448
00:39:21,628 --> 00:39:23,260
Hello.

449
00:39:25,735 --> 00:39:27,448
Now you look like a bride.

450
00:39:28,048 --> 00:39:31,192
- Have changed?
- Yes, and you look much better.

451
00:39:36,503 --> 00:39:38,646
- Where is my chador?
- Over there.

452
00:39:40,809 --> 00:39:43,315
It really changes you,
congratulations.

453
00:39:44,518 --> 00:39:49,340
I'm going to make lunch,
put him down and I'll be back.

454
00:39:49,503 --> 00:39:52,770
Don't bother.
The young lady will do the rest.

455
00:39:53,971 --> 00:39:55,524
Goodbye.

456
00:39:58,197 --> 00:40:01,702
That kid was driving me crazy.
Give me a glass.

457
00:40:02,943 --> 00:40:05,086
If I'm staying, let's get to it.

458
00:40:05,456 --> 00:40:08,994
You have time. You can always
come tomorrow. I'm beat.

459
00:40:09,484 --> 00:40:13,067
- But you'll already be gone!
- Tomorrow, before we leave

460
00:40:14,070 --> 00:40:15,738
You're leaving at 4 a. m.

461
00:40:33,810 --> 00:40:36,919
How do you know that?
Who told you?

462
00:40:37,081 --> 00:40:38,668
Simine.

463
00:40:41,547 --> 00:40:43,179
She knew?

464
00:40:44,856 --> 00:40:47,204
These don't have any hooks in them!

465
00:40:48,406 --> 00:40:50,913
Wait, how does she know?

466
00:40:51,356 --> 00:40:52,787
Come here.

467
00:40:56,621 --> 00:40:57,653
Sit down.

468
00:41:04,597 --> 00:41:06,583
She knew we were leaving at 4?

469
00:41:09,582 --> 00:41:11,057
Think so.

470
00:41:11,655 --> 00:41:14,559
- How did it come up?
- don't remember.

471
00:41:14,766 --> 00:41:17,954
- What do you mean?
- We talked about lots of things.

472
00:41:18,874 --> 00:41:21,018
Why did you bring up our trip?

473
00:41:24,697 --> 00:41:26,966
We talked about
the holidays and trips.

474
00:41:27,129 --> 00:41:29,953
She said that lots of people
are going to Dubai.

475
00:41:30,200 --> 00:41:34,022
She said you were also going
early tomorrow morning.

476
00:41:34,227 --> 00:41:35,861
You said at 4.

477
00:41:36,022 --> 00:41:38,928
- Said early.
- You said at 4!

478
00:41:39,094 --> 00:41:43,438
Meant early.
Before 4 is still night for me.

479
00:41:45,196 --> 00:41:46,465
And what else?

480
00:41:46,630 --> 00:41:50,453
She wanted to know your age
and your husband's job.

481
00:41:51,456 --> 00:41:54,439
- Is that all?
- She isn't very talkative.

482
00:41:57,598 --> 00:42:00,626
She did a good job.
She's talented.

483
00:42:04,178 --> 00:42:05,652
She didn't let me pay.

484
00:42:09,003 --> 00:42:13,111
- You didn't say that you were here?
- didn't say anything.

485
00:42:17,617 --> 00:42:19,919
Should also put up the screens?

486
00:42:21,366 --> 00:42:23,159
Go back to work.

487
